---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import SubscribeCard from '../components/SubscribeCard.astro'
---

<Base
  title="About Enter the Limelight — studio behind Inkwell and Landmark"
  description="Founder note from Steven Spacek Jr. on Enter the Limelight: free local-first Inkwell writing software, Landmark swipe discovery, and building in public."
  keywords="Enter the Limelight, Steven Spacek Jr, Inkwell founder, Landmark app studio"
>
  <main>
    <article class="about">
      <header class="about-head container">
        <p class="eyebrow">A founder's note</p>
        <h1 class="display about-title">Why I'm building Limelight.</h1>
      </header>

      <section class="about-body container">
        <aside class="about-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="about-portrait-frame">
            <div class="about-portrait-tile">
              <span class="about-portrait-initials">SS</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="about-portrait-cap">Steven Spacek Jr.</p>
          <p class="about-portrait-role">Founder, Limelight</p>
        </aside>

        <div class="about-prose">
          <p>
            <a href="/inkwell">Inkwell</a> is the writing app I wish I'd had
            when I was just starting out as an author. I had stories I cared
            about, a few half-good chapters, and a folder full of files that
            wouldn't sit still. Every tool I tried had been built for someone
            further down the road — for the writer with a system, a process, a
            publisher. Not the one staring at chapter one wondering whether it
            should even exist.
          </p>
          <p>
            So I built the tool I needed then, and the tool I still need now:
            chapter-first, local-first, and free. No account wall. No
            subscription. Unlocked EPUB and print-ready PDF when the draft is
            ready. The manuscript stays on your device.
          </p>
          <p>
            <a href="/landmark">Landmark</a> is the studio's second product —
            for the hours when the book can wait. Swipe through historical
            spots, food and drink, and hidden gems near you. Save what you want
            to visit. Skip the rest. Not dating. Just places.
          </p>
          <p>
            Limelight is the small studio around both: mostly me, a handful of
            writers I trust, and an ambition to keep showing up in the
            <a href="/journal">journal</a> with the work on the table.
          </p>
          <p>
            If that sounds like your kind of place, the curtain is up. Pull up
            a seat.
          </p>
          <p class="about-sign">— Steven</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider-rule" />

      <section class="container">
        <SubscribeCard
          eyebrow="Stay close to the work"
          heading="The journal, by email"
          blurb="Notes on Inkwell, Landmark, craft, and the books I'm betting on. Free, occasional, easy to leave."
        />
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem) 0 1rem;
  }

  .about-head {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
  }

  .about-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 3.75rem);
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-body {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
  }

  @media (min-width: 760px) {
    .about-body {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(12rem, 14rem) 1fr;
    }
  }

  .about-portrait {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-portrait-frame {
    width: 11rem;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    margin: 0 auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gold-dim);
    border-radius: 50%;
    padding: 0.5rem;
    background: var(--color-stage-elevated);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-stage), 0 0 24px rgba(160, 27, 42, 0.2);
  }

  .about-portrait-tile {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: radial-gradient(
      circle at 50% 35%,
      rgba(198, 49, 70, 0.7),
      rgba(110, 15, 26, 0.85) 60%,
      rgba(13, 10, 9, 0.95)
    );
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .about-portrait-initials {
    text-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(255, 230, 180, 0.45);
  }

  .about-portrait-cap {
    margin: 0.85rem 0 0.15rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .about-portrait-role {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .about-prose {
    max-width: var(--prose-max);
    color: var(--color-cream);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .about-prose p {
    margin: 0 0 1.15rem;
  }

  .about-sign {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-gold-bright);
  }

</style>
